        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="199" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/11–949: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-09">November 9,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received November 14—1:22 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–2062. [Here follows report on Singapore Conference similar in substance to
                    report given in memorandum of conversation on November 8, printed on <ref target="#pg_184">page 184</ref>.]</p>
                <p>On the afternoon of November 8, Mr. Peter Scarlett, Head of Far Eastern
                    Department, Foreign Office … stated that, although in general the reactions
                    received from the interested friendly governments up to the present were only of
                    a preliminary nature (Embtel 4353, October 31<note n="17" xml:id="d199fn17">Not
                        printed.</note>), on the whole they were sympathetic with the British
                    inclination toward early recognition. Two of the powers consulted had emphasized
                    that it would be embarrassing to recognize the new government before the end of
                    the present session of the UNGA.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
